    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-08-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-08-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="38" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d38">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Terres</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-08-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 2,
                                1895</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 106.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 153, of the 9th
                            ultimo, reporting that the attachment levied by Mr. Devot on the second
                            installment of the indemnity due to Mr. Richard Allen had been raised
                            and the amount paid over to your legation.</p>
                <p>The Department is glad to learn that the matter was amicably
                            arranged.</p>
                <p>Your communication to the Haitian secretary of foreign affairs of the
                            views of this Government in regard to the matter was, however, timely,
                            and will doubtless tend to a better understanding of the subject in the
                            future. You should, however, have sent a copy of your communication.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
